{"title": "Invasion of the Baby Snatchers", "content": "Losing a child is the worst nightmare of many parents. Creators play into this fear by creating characters that steal children for a living. Aliens, evil elves/fairies, goblins and other inhuman creatures are notorious for this. If a human does this, chances are they're a very special kind of evil character, because Children Are Innocent.\n\nThere are many possible motivations for this. Perhaps the abductors have technology that's Powered by a Forsaken Child. Maybe their god demands sacrifice. It could be that they need Child Soldiers or slaves. Maybe they want a child of their own. Or maybe they just think that kids are delicious.\n\nFor a specific variation that involves abduction by fairy beings, see Changeling Tale. See also Alien Abduction, Eats Babies, Childless Dystopia.\n\nThe name is a pun on Invasion of the Body Snatchers which is more of an Assimilation Plot than child kidnapping.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvasionOfTheBabySnatchers", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TorchwoodChildrenOfEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/InvasionOfTheBodySnatchers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SailorMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DetectiveConan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PrincessTutu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/GreenLantern", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/VertigoComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BatmanNoMansLand", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/XFactor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/CourtneyCrumrinAndTheNightThings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TarotWitchOfTheBlackRose", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SympathyForLadyVengeance", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BatmanReturns", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MonstersInc", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ChittyChittyBangBang", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCityOfLostChildren", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Labyrinth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GhostbustersII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ThePiedPiperOfHamelin"